Female terminalia (
Figs 28–30
) with unusually long and rod-like cerci. Basal segment of cerci almost twice as long as epiproct and 1.5 times as long as distal segment, both almost rod-like. Proctiger subtriangular on ventral surface as well, tergite 9 reduced into symmetrical lateral remnants, genital furca with open middle aperture and very slender posterolateral apendages. Length: body 18.0 mm, wing 15.3 mm .
